args: So I think I have to leave the Halidom for\na bit, Prince {player_name}.
I'm going to visit my mother's grave.
No. We used to go together every year,\nbut I decided to go on my own this time.
Hmm. I imagine you might run into fiends\non the way. How about I come with you?
Can you let me go on my own? Please?\nLouise said it was okay and everything!
It's a great chance for me to see if my\ntraining has been paying off.
Don't worry! I'll be back home safe and\nsound before anyone even knows I'm gone.
Well, if you're decided, I won't stop you.\nBe safe, Lowen.
Oh man, I don't feel like things took quite\nthis long when I came here with Louise.
I think I'm lost—and that isn't good at ALL.
Wait, no! I can't! I have to get stronger!
The prince would never turn back!
Think, Lowen! Okay, at a time like this,\nRanzal would tell a really funny joke or\nsomething to lighten the mood.
...Oh, it's just a little bird. Aw, it's hurt!
I don't think it can fly right now. But if it\nstays here, some fiend is gonna find it\nand eat it for a snack!
(It's a fiend! And man, is it ever BIG...)
(I can still get away if I go now, but I'd\nhave to leave that little bird behind.)
(Louise never ran away when she had to\nprotect me.)
(No matter how badly she was hurt,\nshe always stuck it out.)
(And if I want to become an adult who can\nprotect people like she did...)
Hey, you stupid fiend! If you're gonna\nfight someone, have a piece of ME!
I'm way braver than you—my sister taught\nme that!
And the prince taught me how to fight!
I'm strong now, and I'm not gonna lose.\nSO COME AT ME, BRO! YAAAAAAAH!
I'm worried about Lowen—I do hope that\nhe's all right.
It's only been three days since he set off,\nyeah? Ain't no reason to panic yet.
Three days is already far longer than such\na trip should take.
I TOLD ya, yer worrying too much!\nHave a little faith in the kid already.
I agree. We need to believe in Lowen.
We were so worried about you.
Heh. I figured as much. But hey,\nI did it, right?!
Thanks! Oh, and I also realized something\non this trip.
Until now, I thought that if I was still a\nlittle brother, I couldn't be an adult.
Even if I separate from my sister and\nbecome independent, it won't change\nthe fact I'm her little bro.
In fact, that's the whole reason I want\nto be strong in the first place!
I guess even little brothers can get\nstrong, huh?
And furthermore, you and Louise have an\nexceptionally powerful bond.
That bond drives both of you to be the best\npeople you can be.
Hey, that's right! ...Although I didn't do\nthis ALL just for her.
I did it for you guys as well, because\nyou've all helped me out so much.
Even though we were apart, we were\nstill connected. I was never really alone.
That is a fascinating way to look at it.
I think I understand. I've often had times\nwhere the face of someone I care about\nhas come to me in a time of crisis.
Oh man, this kid is blowin' my MIND\nright now.
Hee hee! Yeah, but I still have a long way\nto go.
So I'm gonna bust my butt to become an\neven cooler adult! Er, along with all of you,\nof course.
Oh, by the way, I brought back some\nmeat from my trip.
How about I try cooking it up into\nsomething we can all enjoy?
Are you certain that's a good idea?
You're the one who taught me how to do\nkitchen stuff, Cleo. Believe in your student!
A jest only, I assure you. I can't wait to try\nwhatever you make.
Then get ready, because I'm gonna be the\nbest at cooking and housework AND\nfighting!
I'm gonna grow in a ton of ways and be\nthe little brother everyone can count on!
